Quote: The Smith Family Trust is winding up after 75 years of charity work in Wellington... The charity originated in Australia in 1922... One of its first projects was the milk in schools programme, which was taken over by the government in the 1940s. The charity might also have been involved in setting up the first child dental health clinics and running a soup kitchen during the Depression.
